   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE TRAINING AND THE PRACTICE OF THE VITAL GROUPS MESSAGE ONE TO BE VITALIZED Scripture Reading: Rom 12:1a; Rev 2:4, 12-15, 24, 20; 3:1-2, 15-16, 17-20; 2:7, 11, 17, 26-29; 3:5-6, 12-13, 21-22; Rom 12:1-2, 11; Rev 14:1-5; 21:1-2 OUTLINE The cause: The compassions of God Rom 12:1a.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The degradation of the church: The church in general: Having left her first love for the Lord Rev 2:4.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Having married herself to the world and become satanic, full of the hierarchical teaching Rev 2:12-15.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The Catholic Church: Having become demonic Rev 2:24.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Full of fornication and idolatry Rev 2:20.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The Protestant churches: Having been deadened and being dying Rev 3:1-2a.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Not complete in anything Rev 3:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Brethren: Lukewarm, spewed out of the Lord's mouth Rev 3:15-16.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Self-contented, yet wretched, miserable, poor, blind, naked, and Christless Rev 3:17-20.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The calling of the Lord in the age of the overcomers Rev 2:7, 11, 17, 26-29; 3:5-6, 12-13, 21-22.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The purpose: To respond to the Lord's calling.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>For the Lord's recovery in this age pay attention to the seven crucial points of the major items of the Lord's recovery today .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>For the building up of the Body of Christ through the proper practice of the local churches: On the local ground in the oneness of the unique Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>By: Saving sinners to be the members of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Feeding the newborn members.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Perfecting the saints.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Prophesying to build up the local churches for the consummation of the building up of the Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The way: To be stirred up in the first love for the Lord through repenting prayers.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>To make a thorough confession to the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>To have close, intimate, and thorough fellowship with the Lord and with the seeking saints.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>To reconsecrate yourself to the Lord: In presenting your body as a living sacrifice to the Lord Rom 12:1.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>In being transformed by the renewing of the mind from being fashioned according to this age Rom 12:2.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>In not being slothful in zeal, but burning in spirit to serve the Lord Rom 12:11.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>To be the overcomers in the church life: In the age of the overcomers according to the Lord's calling.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>As today's Zion in today's Jerusalem the church life Rev 14:1-5: The high peak, the center, the uplifting, the strengthening, the enriching, and the reality of the church, the holy city.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>To consummate the holy city the church and to bring in the consummated New Jerusalem in eternity Rev 21:1-2.</S>
   </TEXT>
